Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt, the Virgin is seated with the Christ Child on her knee who takes dates from a cloth held by a young man, Joseph collects dates from the tree above that is lowered by five putti, after Giulio Campi. 1580s Engraving printed from two plates
Curator's comments: This is the second state with the publisher's address added. It is related to a painting by Giulio Campi for San Paolo, Milan, painted 1565-70. See 'The Engravings of Giorgio Ghisi', Metropolitan Museum New York, 1985, pp.192-194.
Bibliographic references: Lewis 1985 / The Engravings of Giorgio Ghisi (59.II)
Bellini 1998 / L'Opera incisa di Giorgio Ghisi (61)
